Change IP of Linux/yocto system.

--------------------------------------------------
In this example no external (third-party) library is used.
Everything comes from:
    C++17 standard library headers
        <string>, <iostream>, <sstream>, <fstream>, <cstring>

    POSIX / Linux system headers
        <sys/ioctl.h>, <net/if.h>, <arpa/inet.h>, <unistd.h>

    The Linux ip command (invoked through std::system)
        This is part of the iproute2 package that’s present on almost all Linux/Yocto systems.

So you don’t need to install any special C++ library.
Just make sure your Yocto build includes:
    libc (for the POSIX calls—already present in any normal image)
    iproute2 utilities if you want to actually change the network settings.


------------------------------------------------------
g++ -std=c++17 main.cpp NetworkConfig.cpp -o netconfig
sudo ./netconfig      # needs root to change settings

------------------------------------------------------
$ ethtool eth0 | grep "Link detected"
        Link detected: yes


Continuous Monitoring

watch command
watch -n1 cat /sys/class/net/eth0/carrier

NetworkManager tools (if your Yocto image includes it)
nmcli device status
